"{\"uid\": \"theinertia.com-surf-jack-robinson-olympic-surfing-ocean\", \"noun_phrases\": [{\"sentence\": \"We are not there with wave pool yet, says the West Oz native.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 61, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"wave pool\", \"from\": 22, \"to\": 31}, {\"ngram\": \"the West Oz native\", \"from\": 42, \"to\": 60}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Photo: ISA It turns out I am not alone in thinking Olympic surfing should not take place in wave pools.In a recent op-ed,I disagreed with two world champions, Gabriel Medina and Filipe Toledo.\", \"from\": 62, \"to\": 255, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 222, \"end\": 236, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gabriel_Medina\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Gabriel Medina\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gabriel_Medina\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gabriel_Medina\"}, {\"begin\": 241, \"end\": 254, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Filipe_Toledo\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Filipe Toledo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Filipe_Toledo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Filipe_Toledo\"}, {\"begin\": 241, \"end\": 254, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Filipe_Toledo\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Filipe Toledo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Filipe_Toledo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Filipe_Toledo\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"ISA\", \"from\": 69, \"to\": 72}, {\"ngram\": \"Olympic surfing\", \"from\": 113, \"to\": 128}, {\"ngram\": \"place\", \"from\": 145, \"to\": 150}, {\"ngram\": \"wave pools\", \"from\": 154, \"to\": 164}, {\"ngram\": \"a recent op-ed\", \"from\": 168, \"to\": 182}, {\"ngram\": \"two world champions\", \"from\": 200, \"to\": 219}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They both clamored for an Olympic wave pool following the 2024 Olympics in Tahiti.\", \"from\": 256, \"to\": 338, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 331, \"end\": 337, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tahiti\", \"score\": 0.999999946354366, \"rank\": 5.363974027767567e-08, \"text\": \"Tahiti\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tahiti\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tahiti\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"an Olympic wave pool\", \"from\": 279, \"to\": 299}, {\"ngram\": \"the 2024 Olympics\", \"from\": 310, \"to\": 327}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Many on the internet were quite correctly asking who the hell I thought I was disagreeing with such distinguished surfers.\", \"from\": 339, \"to\": 461, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the internet\", \"from\": 347, \"to\": 359}, {\"ngram\": \"the hell\", \"from\": 392, \"to\": 400}, {\"ngram\": \"such distinguished surfers\", \"from\": 434, \"to\": 460}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But thankfully, Jack Robinson has rushed to my aid.\", \"from\": 462, \"to\": 513, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 478, \"end\": 482, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jack_Shephard\", \"score\": 0.9386373765639355, \"rank\": 0.06492926756571017, \"text\": \"Jack\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jack_Shephard\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jack_Shephard\"}, {\"begin\": 483, \"end\": 491, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Harold_E._Robinson\", \"score\": 0.8493428570218489, \"rank\": 0.15911980792066605, \"text\": \"Robinson\", \"types\": [\"Q901\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Harold_E._Robinson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Harold_E._Robinson\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"my aid\", \"from\": 506, \"to\": 512}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Robinson was quoted in theSydney Morning Heraldwith a scathing review of wave pools, saying pools \\\"are not great to watch,\\\" \\\"boring\\\" and \\\"repetitive,\\\" and that they completely remove the skill of understanding the ocean from competition.\", \"from\": 515, \"to\": 752, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 515, \"end\": 523, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Harold_E._Robinson\", \"score\": 0.8493428570218489, \"rank\": 0.15911980792066605, \"text\": \"Robinson\", \"types\": [\"Q901\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Harold_E._Robinson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Harold_E._Robinson\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"theSydney Morning Heraldwith\", \"from\": 538, \"to\": 566}, {\"ngram\": \"a scathing review\", \"from\": 567, \"to\": 584}, {\"ngram\": \"wave pools\", \"from\": 588, \"to\": 598}, {\"ngram\": \"pools\", \"from\": 607, \"to\": 612}, {\"ngram\": \"the skill\", \"from\": 698, \"to\": 707}, {\"ngram\": \"the ocean\", \"from\": 725, \"to\": 734}, {\"ngram\": \"competition\", \"from\": 740, \"to\": 751}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Here's the full quote: \\\"Personally, if an [Olympic] host country has waves, then use them.\", \"from\": 754, \"to\": 845, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the full quote\", \"from\": 761, \"to\": 775}, {\"ngram\": \"an [Olympic] host country\", \"from\": 793, \"to\": 818}, {\"ngram\": \"waves\", \"from\": 823, \"to\": 828}]}, {\"sentence\": \"America has waves in Hawaii and California.\", \"from\": 846, \"to\": 889, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 867, \"end\": 873, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hawaii\", \"score\": 0.9999988781930296, \"rank\": 1.0794099512850482e-06, \"text\": \"Hawaii\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hawaii\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hawaii\"}, {\"begin\": 878, \"end\": 888, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/California\", \"score\": 0.999996210642752, \"rank\": 2.623448047706989e-06, \"text\": \"California\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/California\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/California\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"America\", \"from\": 846, \"to\": 853}, {\"ngram\": \"waves\", \"from\": 858, \"to\": 863}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Some people might prefer a wave pool because it suits their surfing but to me, working out the ocean is a big part of competitive surfing.\", \"from\": 890, \"to\": 1028, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Some people\", \"from\": 890, \"to\": 901}, {\"ngram\": \"a wave pool\", \"from\": 915, \"to\": 926}, {\"ngram\": \"their surfing\", \"from\": 944, \"to\": 957}, {\"ngram\": \"the ocean\", \"from\": 981, \"to\": 990}, {\"ngram\": \"a big part\", \"from\": 994, \"to\": 1004}, {\"ngram\": \"competitive surfing\", \"from\": 1008, \"to\": 1027}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It's such a skill and you take that away in a wave pool.\\\"\", \"from\": 1029, \"to\": 1086, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"such a skill\", \"from\": 1034, \"to\": 1046}, {\"ngram\": \"a wave pool\", \"from\": 1073, \"to\": 1084}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"And from a spectator point of view, personally I do not think wave pools are great to watch.\", \"from\": 1088, \"to\": 1181, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a spectator point\", \"from\": 1098, \"to\": 1115}, {\"ngram\": \"view\", \"from\": 1119, \"to\": 1123}, {\"ngram\": \"wave pools\", \"from\": 1151, \"to\": 1161}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Maybe one day they will be.\", \"from\": 1182, \"to\": 1209, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But right now, I think it's very repetitive to watch.\", \"from\": 1210, \"to\": 1263, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Mostly the waves can only handle so much size and if a wave's quite long it gets boring, it's the same maneuvers and moves over and over again.\", \"from\": 1264, \"to\": 1407, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the waves\", \"from\": 1271, \"to\": 1280}, {\"ngram\": \"so much size\", \"from\": 1297, \"to\": 1309}, {\"ngram\": \"a wave\", \"from\": 1317, \"to\": 1323}, {\"ngram\": \"the same maneuvers\", \"from\": 1358, \"to\": 1376}, {\"ngram\": \"moves\", \"from\": 1381, \"to\": 1386}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I am not writing off wave pools, I think one day they will have their place.\", \"from\": 1408, \"to\": 1484, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"wave pools\", \"from\": 1429, \"to\": 1439}, {\"ngram\": \"their place\", \"from\": 1472, \"to\": 1483}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But right now, for the Olympics, I do not think so.\\\"\", \"from\": 1485, \"to\": 1537, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 1504, \"to\": 1516}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Robinson was one of the surfers most affected by the unpredictable nature of the ocean at the Olympics.\", \"from\": 1539, \"to\": 1642, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1539, \"end\": 1547, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Harold_E._Robinson\", \"score\": 0.8493428570218489, \"rank\": 0.15911980792066605, \"text\": \"Robinson\", \"types\": [\"Q901\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Harold_E._Robinson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Harold_E._Robinson\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the surfers\", \"from\": 1559, \"to\": 1570}, {\"ngram\": \"the unpredictable nature\", \"from\": 1588, \"to\": 1612}, {\"ngram\": \"the ocean\", \"from\": 1616, \"to\": 1625}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 1629, \"to\": 1641}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In the men's final he was left stranded for the better part of the heat waiting for a good wave to get back in the running for gold.\", \"from\": 1643, \"to\": 1775, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the better part\", \"from\": 1687, \"to\": 1702}, {\"ngram\": \"the heat\", \"from\": 1706, \"to\": 1714}, {\"ngram\": \"a good wave\", \"from\": 1727, \"to\": 1738}, {\"ngram\": \"the running\", \"from\": 1754, \"to\": 1765}, {\"ngram\": \"gold\", \"from\": 1770, \"to\": 1774}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But the wave never came.\", \"from\": 1776, \"to\": 1800, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the wave\", \"from\": 1780, \"to\": 1788}]}, {\"sentence\": \"So Robinson coming out against the wave pool idea is a strong counterpunch to the media push by Medina and Toledo.\", \"from\": 1801, \"to\": 1915, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1804, \"end\": 1812, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Harold_E._Robinson\", \"score\": 0.8493428570218489, \"rank\": 0.15911980792066605, \"text\": \"Robinson\", \"types\": [\"Q901\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Harold_E._Robinson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Harold_E._Robinson\"}, {\"begin\": 1897, \"end\": 1903, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Medina\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.925598837452843e-19, \"text\": \"Medina\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Medina\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Medina\"}, {\"begin\": 1908, \"end\": 1914, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Toledo_Rockets_football\", \"score\": 0.928528552569206, \"rank\": 0.0417290580645165, \"text\": \"Toledo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Toledo_Rockets_football\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Toledo_Rockets_football\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the wave pool idea\", \"from\": 1832, \"to\": 1850}, {\"ngram\": \"a strong counterpunch\", \"from\": 1854, \"to\": 1875}, {\"ngram\": \"the media push\", \"from\": 1879, \"to\": 1893}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Robinson and I align on another key pointI got into during my opinion piece.It's not that wave pools will never be the answer.\", \"from\": 1917, \"to\": 2043, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1917, \"end\": 1925, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Harold_E._Robinson\", \"score\": 0.8493428570218489, \"rank\": 0.15911980792066605, \"text\": \"Robinson\", \"types\": [\"Q901\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Harold_E._Robinson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Harold_E._Robinson\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"another key pointI\", \"from\": 1941, \"to\": 1959}, {\"ngram\": \"my opinion piece\", \"from\": 1976, \"to\": 1992}, {\"ngram\": \"wave pools\", \"from\": 2007, \"to\": 2017}, {\"ngram\": \"the answer\", \"from\": 2032, \"to\": 2042}]}, {\"sentence\": \"With the pool technology that exists right now and the runway of Los Angeles in 2028 and Brisbane in 2032, there is not a need to drydock the Olympic surfing event on land.\", \"from\": 2044, \"to\": 2216, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2109, \"end\": 2120, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"score\": 0.9999997650702702, \"rank\": 1.3788781148742236e-07, \"text\": \"Los Angeles\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\"}, {\"begin\": 2133, \"end\": 2141, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brisbane\", \"score\": 0.9998914096807872, \"rank\": 0.00010056764161714978, \"text\": \"Brisbane\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brisbane\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brisbane\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the pool technology\", \"from\": 2049, \"to\": 2068}, {\"ngram\": \"the runway\", \"from\": 2095, \"to\": 2105}, {\"ngram\": \"a need\", \"from\": 2164, \"to\": 2170}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympic surfing event\", \"from\": 2182, \"to\": 2207}, {\"ngram\": \"land\", \"from\": 2211, \"to\": 2215}]}, {\"sentence\": \"One day pool technology will get to that point.\", \"from\": 2217, \"to\": 2264, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"One day pool technology\", \"from\": 2217, \"to\": 2240}, {\"ngram\": \"that point\", \"from\": 2253, \"to\": 2263}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Or maybe in 2036 the Olympics will be held in a landlocked country.\", \"from\": 2265, \"to\": 2332, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 2282, \"to\": 2294}, {\"ngram\": \"a landlocked country\", \"from\": 2311, \"to\": 2331}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But coming off the back of the excitement and success of Teahupo'o, now's not the time to switch up the winning formula of ocean surfing.\", \"from\": 2333, \"to\": 2470, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the back\", \"from\": 2348, \"to\": 2356}, {\"ngram\": \"the excitement\", \"from\": 2360, \"to\": 2374}, {\"ngram\": \"success\", \"from\": 2379, \"to\": 2386}, {\"ngram\": \"Teahupo'o\", \"from\": 2390, \"to\": 2399}, {\"ngram\": \"the time\", \"from\": 2411, \"to\": 2419}, {\"ngram\": \"the winning formula\", \"from\": 2433, \"to\": 2452}, {\"ngram\": \"ocean surfing\", \"from\": 2456, \"to\": 2469}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Robinson endorses this logic.\", \"from\": 2471, \"to\": 2500, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2471, \"end\": 2479, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Harold_E._Robinson\", \"score\": 0.8493428570218489, \"rank\": 0.15911980792066605, \"text\": \"Robinson\", \"types\": [\"Q901\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Harold_E._Robinson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Harold_E._Robinson\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"this logic\", \"from\": 2489, \"to\": 2499}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Only the best.\", \"from\": 2502, \"to\": 2516, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"We promise.\", \"from\": 2517, \"to\": 2528, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Join our community of contributors.\", \"from\": 2530, \"to\": 2565, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"our community\", \"from\": 2535, \"to\": 2548}, {\"ngram\": \"contributors\", \"from\": 2552, \"to\": 2564}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Inertia is part ofAllGear Digital'sportfolio of media brands.\", \"from\": 2567, \"to\": 2632, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The Inertia\", \"from\": 2567, \"to\": 2578}, {\"ngram\": \"part of